result.execSummary:
The defendant Tony Lydell Winston was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Throw/Discharge Bodily Fluid at Public Safety Worker, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.375(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Tony Lydell Winston in court with attorney Alexis R Liggins.  Defendant Tony Lydell Winston in custody.  Tyrone M St Junior appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO COUNT 3:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting. 

AS TO COUNTS 1, 2, AND 4:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and state's motion, the Court ordered Counts 1, 2, and 4 DISMISSED AND READ-IN for the purpose of sentencing in Count 3.

AS TO COUNT 3:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 10 MONTHS in the House of Correction, CONCURRENT with 13CM003770, CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence, with credit for 119 DAYS time served and Huber privileges for any HOC work program and work search.

The Court ordered the defendant to pay all applicable mandatory costs, surcharges and assessments by 6-09-15; any balance remaining unpaid at that time is to be converted to a civil judgment against the defendant.  The Court ordered the defendant to provide a DNA sample - pay surcharge.
Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.
